text.tspan: Electricty production by source, United Kingdom
Electricity production in the United Kingdom by source, measured in gigawatt-hours (GWh) per year. 'Other fuels'
refers refers to additional sources including coke, coke oven gas, blast furnace gas, waste products from chemical
processes, refuse derived fuels, and other renewables.
Source: UK Department for Energy and Climate Change (DECC).
